  "text": "The Prometheus Alertmanager notification pipeline in Grafana Mimir follows this flow:\n\n**1. Alert Ingestion (dispatch/dispatch.go):**\nAlerts are ingested into the system and stored in a provider (mem.Alerts). The Dispatcher.Run() method (line 147 in dispatch.go) initiates the pipeline by subscribing to incoming alerts via provider.AlertIterator. The run() method (line 161) continuously polls for new alerts from the iterator.\n\n**2. Routing Tree Traversal (dispatch/route.go):**\nOnce an alert arrives, the Dispatcher calls route.Match(alert.Labels) (line 211 in dispatch.go) which traverses the routing tree defined in dispatch/route.go. The Match() function (line 147 in route.go) performs a depth-first left-to-right search through the tree, returning all matching route nodes where the alert should be sent.\n\n**3. Dispatcher Processing (dispatch/dispatch.go):**\nFor each matching route, the dispatcher calls processAlert() (line 344) which determines the aggregation group for the alert and schedules notifications via the notify Stage pipeline.\n\n**4. Notification Pipeline Stages (notify/notify.go):**\nThe PipelineBuilder.New() method (line 395 in notify.go) constructs the notification pipeline with the following stages in order:\n- GossipSettleStage: Waits for cluster state to settle\n- MuteStage with Inhibitor: Checks inhibition rules\n- TimeActiveStage: Checks if current time is within active intervals\n- TimeMuteStage: Checks if current time is within mute intervals  \n- MuteStage with Silencer: Checks active silences\n- Receiver-specific stages: Deduplication, retry, and final notification dispatch\n\n**5. Inhibition Check (inhibit/inhibit.go):**\nThe Inhibitor.Mutes() method (line 128) checks if an alert matches any inhibition rules. Source alerts matching SourceMatchers are cached, and target alerts matching TargetMatchers are checked against these cached source alerts. If both source and target matchers match and required labels are equal, the alert is inhibited.\n\n**6. Silence Check (silence/silence.go):**\nThe Silencer.Mutes() method (line 113) queries the Silences store to check if the alert's labels match any active or pending silence matchers. It maintains a marker cache for efficiency, only doing full queries when new silences are added.\n\n**7. Final Notifier Dispatch (notify/notify.go):**\nAfter passing all checks, the RetryStage.Exec() method (line 791) attempts to send notifications to the configured integration notifiers (email, slack, webhook, etc.) with exponential backoff retry logic. The SetNotifiesStage logs successful notifications to prevent duplicates.\n\n**Orchestration (pkg/alertmanager/alertmanager.go):**\nThe Alertmanager.ApplyConfig() method (line 493) orchestrates the entire pipeline by:\n1. Creating the routing tree from config (line 537)\n2. Instantiating the Inhibitor with rules (line 513)\n3. Building the notification pipeline (line 557)\n4. Creating the Dispatcher with the pipeline (line 567)\n5. Starting the Dispatcher and Inhibitor as background goroutines (lines 579-580)"
